  • Method Details

    • group

      Stream<Subgroup<I,O>> group(List<I> inputs)
      Group the inputs provided into sensible subgroups. The grouper may drop input or assign the same input to multiple groups; it should not include the same input in the same group multiple times
      Parameters:
      inputs - the inputs to be grouped; the list is now owned by the grouper and the grouper can change it
      Returns:
      the groups produced. For each output group, the collection function is provided. This is a (possibly modified) operation that collects input data into the output. The grouper will receive a template for this operation at construction.
